      "content": "i dont need the emergency services, i'm not dying i just have bad back pain lol. i'm just asking a simple question about how the meds work. if i take some aspirin along with the ibuprofen, does the combination actually increase the pain relief because they work on different pathways? or is it just redundant? i really need to know if it's a safe way to get some actual relief since the 800mg didnt even touch it.",
